The paper proposes a deep neural network for saliency detection, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes multi-scale feature maps and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in deep learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on enhancing local and global information in different layers, which is a common problem in deep learning and machine learning, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper also uses a recurrent structure and self-attention module, which are common techniques in neural networks, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with saliency detection, which is a task related to information retrieval and image processing, indicating cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
